The Beijing authorities lifted a series of COVID-19 control and prevention measures on June 6, as most districts in the Chinese capital reported no community-level COVID-19 transmission for at least a week. Restaurants and cafes resumed dine-in services, except for establishments in Fengtai and parts of Changping districts. How was indoor dining on the first day back? CGTN stringer went to the commercial district and food courts in Beijing and talked to residents and restaurant staff.